org.ensembl.datamodel
Interface MiscSet

All Superinterfaces:
Persistent, java.io.Serializable
public interface MiscSet
extends Persistent

MiscSets represent classsifications or groupings of MiscFeatures. Features are classified into sets essentially to define what they are and how they may be used. Generally MiscFeatures are retrieved on the basis of their associated sets.

Author:
Craig Melsopp
See Also:
MiscSetAdaptor, MiscFeature, MiscFeatureAdaptor
